The Importance of Version Control in Software Development
In the fast-paced world of software development, where teams collaborate on projects and codebases are continuously evolving, maintaining organization and efficiency is crucial. One of the most vital tools for achieving this is version control. This article delves into what version control is, its significance, and best practices for using it effectively.

What is Version Control?
Version control is a system that tracks changes to files over time. It allows developers to manage changes to source code, collaborate with others, and revert to previous versions when necessary. The most commonly used version control system today is Git, along with platforms like GitHub, GitLab, and Bitbucket.
